accessibility.text: After a lapse of seventy-two years from the enumeration date of a decennial census, the National Archives and Records service may disclose information contained in these records for use in legitimate historical, genealogical or other worth-while research, provided adequate precautions are taken to make sure that the information disclosed is not used for the detriment of any of the persons whose records are involved.
